In this press briefing, Sarah Sanders, the White House Press Secretary, begins by acknowledging the anniversary of the attack on Pearl Harbor and the President's meeting with Pearl Harbor veterans. She then discusses the upcoming meeting between President Trump and congressional leaders to discuss funding the government, particularly the military and the Department of Veterans Affairs. Sanders highlights stories of generosity and love during the Christmas season, including the story of St. Matthew's Episcopal Church in West Virginia. She also addresses various questions, including those on the possible government shutdown, the California wildfires, John Bolton's visit to the White House, Donald Trump Jr.'s conversations with the President, sexual misconduct allegations, the recognition of Jerusalem as the capital of Israel, additional sanctions on North Korea, the Winter Olympics, tax reform, the FBI, and the peace process in the Middle East. Sanders concludes by mentioning the President's event with Pearl Harbor survivors and the upcoming congressional meeting.